HEADWORD: Guardhouse
<hw>Guard"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A building which is occupied by the guard, and in which soldiers
are confined for misconduct; hence, a lock-up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

